        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 23</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num023-P253r-L13_trl" n="13"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.004.022.trl.xml#Num022-P253r-L13_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             Balaam said to Balak, ‘Build me here seven altars
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             and prepare me here seven oxen and seven rams.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="2">And Balak did as Balaam had spoken. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             Balak and Balaam offered on every altar an ox and a ram.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="3">And Balaam said to Balak, ‘Stand by your burnt offering,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             and I will go. Maybe the Lord’s word will come to meet me, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             whatever word he shows me, I will tell you, too.’
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             And he went up.</l>
                        <l n="4">And the angel met Balaam,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="253v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             and he said to him, ‘I have prepared seven altars and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             offered burnt offering: on each altar a bullock and a ram.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="5">And the Lord put a word in Balaam’s mouth, and said,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             ‘Return to Balak, and thus you shall speak.’</l>
                        <l n="6">And he returned to him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             and, lo, he stood by his burnt offering, he and all the rulers of
                            Moab.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="7">And he took up his parable, and said, ‘Balak has led me from Aram,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             Moab’s king from the mountains of the east, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             “Come, curse Jacob for me, and come, slander Israel!’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="8">How shall I curse that which God has not cursed? And how shall I
                            slander
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             that which the Lord has not slandered?</l>
                        <l n="9">Because from the top of the rocks I see
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             him, and from the rocks I look out for him: lo, a people dwelling alone
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             and not reckoning itself among the kingdoms.</l>
                        <l n="10">Who
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             can count the dust of Jacob, and who can number
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             the fourth part of Israel? May my soul die
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             the death of the upright, and let my last end be like his!’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="11">And Balak said to Balaam, ‘What have you done to me?
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             I took you to curse my enemies, and, lo, you have blessed them!’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="12">And Balaam answered and said,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             ‘Lo, I will watch out to say that which the Lord has put in my
                            mouth.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="13">And Balak said to him, ‘Come, now, with me
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             to another place from which you may see them.
                            <milestone unit="page" n="254r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             You will see only the |outer| edge of them, and you will not see them
                            all. And curse them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             from there for me.’</l>
                        <l n="14">And he brought him <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-023-seg001_trl" />to the field of watchmen<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="Num-023-seg001_trl" /><ref n="1"
                                target="#Num-023-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" />,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-023-seg002_trl" />to the top of the
                                summit<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-023-seg002_trl" /><ref
                                n="2" target="#Num-023-fn2_trl" type="noteAnchor" />, and he built
                            seven altars and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             offered burnt offering: on each altar an ox and a ram.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="15">And he said to Balak, ‘Stand here by your burnt offering,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             and I will meet the Lord yonder.’</l>
                        <l n="16">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             the angel of Lord met Balaam and put a word in his mouth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             and said, ‘Return to Balak, and thus you shall speak.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="17">And he came to him, and, lo, he stood by his burnt offering,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and the rulers of Moab with him. And Balak said to him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             ‘What has the Lord spoken?’</l>
                        <l n="18">And he took up his
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             parable, and said, ‘Rise up, Balak, and hear. Hearken to me,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             oh you, son of Zippor:</l>
                        <l n="19">God is not like a man,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             that he should lie, neither like the son of man, that he should repent.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             Has he said, and will he not do it? Or has he spoken, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             will he not consolidate it?</l>
                        <l n="20">Lo, I have taken
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             an advice to bless, and the one who is blessed, and I cannot give it
                            back.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="21">He has not spotted wickedness in Jacob,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             and he has not seen fault in Israel. The Lord God’s help
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             is with him, and the shout of a king is in it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                        <l n="22">God who brought them out from Egypt <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-023-seg003_trl" />has
                            <milestone unit="page" n="254v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             given him strength<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-023-seg003_trl"
                                 /><ref n="3" target="#Num-023-fn3_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> like
                            the strength of a rhinoceros, <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-023-seg004_trl" />so that his enemies were not able
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             to grow stronger<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-023-seg004_trl"
                                 /><ref n="4" target="#Num-023-fn4_trl" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="23">For there is no divination
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-023-seg005_trl" />against
                                Jacob<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-023-seg005_trl" /><ref
                                n="5" target="#Num-023-fn5_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> and there is no
                            witchcraft <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-023-seg006_trl" />against
                                Israel<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-023-seg006_trl" /><ref
                                n="6" target="#Num-023-fn6_trl" type="noteAnchor" />, <seg
                                type="commented" corresp="#Num-023-seg007_trl" />when
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             they wish to know the future matters.<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Num-023-seg007_trl" /><ref n="7" target="#Num-023-fn7_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> It is said to Jacob
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             and to Israel, <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-023-seg008_trl"
                             />through a prophet,<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Num-023-seg008_trl" /><ref n="8" target="#Num-023-fn8_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> “What will God do?”.</l>
                        <l n="24">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             Lo, the people dwell like a lioness, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             they lift up themselves like a lion. It does not lie down until it eats
                            the prey
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             and drinks the blood of the slain.’</l>
                        <l n="25">And Balak said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             to Balaam, ‘Do not curse them nor even bless
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             them at all.’</l>
                        <l n="26">But Balaam answered and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             said to Balak, ‘Did I not speak to you, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             “All that the Lord speaks, that I will do?”’</l>
                        <l n="27">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             Balak <supplied reason="lost">said</supplied> to Balaam, ‘Come now, I
                            will take you to another place.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             Maybe it will seem honest in the eyes of God, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             you shall curse them from there for me.’</l>
                        <l n="28">And Balak took
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             Balaam to the top of Peor that looks toward
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             Jeshimon<ref n="9" target="#Num-023-fn9_trl" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="29">And Balaam said to Balak,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             ‘Build me here seven altars and prepare me
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             here seven oxen and seven rams.’</l>
                        <l n="30">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             Balak did as Balaam had said and offered burnt offering: an ox
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num023-P254v-L21_trl" n="21"
                                next="ADub.III.73.004.024.trl.xml#Num024-P254v-L21_trl" />
                             and a ram on each altar. </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
